      <section eId="sec_170_50">
        <num>170.50</num>
        <heading>Unlawfully using slugs; definitions of terms</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_170_50__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>to\nreceive a coin or bill or a token made for the purpose, and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_170_50__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>in\nreturn for the insertion or deposit thereof, automatically to offer, to\nprovide, to assist in providing or to permit the acquisition of some\nproperty or some service.\n  2. "Slug" means an object or article which, by virtue of its size,\nshape or any other quality, is capable of being inserted or deposited in\na coin machine as an improper substitute for a genuine coin, bill or\ntoken.\n  3. "Value" of a slug means the value of the coin, bill or token for\nwhich it is capable of being substituted.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
